President Obama and Chancellor Merkel spoke on the phone to discuss the tragic downing of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17. They expressed condolences for the victims and emphasized the need for all parties to allow international investigators full access to the incident site. They also discussed the actions taken by the US and the EU against individuals and entities, including those from Russia, involved in destabilizing Ukraine. They agreed to continue efforts for a diplomatic solution and stressed Russia's responsibility to deny separatists access to weapons and support from within Russia.